The paper deals with polynomial approximations to boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the derandomization of concentration inequalities, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and probability (cs.PR). The techniques used in the paper come from weighted approximation theory, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and approximation algorithms (cs.DS).
